The file QR.tar.gz is a tarball of projects/book.cup and was
uploaded to the ftp.cup.org ftp site July 3, 2004.  It purports
to contain the full monte needed to recreate the QR ms.

The file QRx.tar.gz is a tarball of projects/book -- the .tex files
differ only in that they contain the \index{} entries needed to
make the (two) indices.  The full ms.  should be creatible by the
following incantations on some reasonable facsimile of a unix box:

	tar xfz QRz.tar.gz
	make
	make all

N.B.  The QRx tarball contains quite a few extra files  that were purged
prior making the QR version.  These shouldn't create any inconsistencies
in the typeset versions.  I resolutely resisted all temptations to change
the latex files, except by introducing index entries.  I can't insure
that something wasn't inadvertantly altered, but I would hope that the
probability of this was quite small.


The file book.pdf is the pdf version of the current manuscript.

The file bookx.pdf is the pdf version of the current manuscript with indices.
